Great! Now I can see the existing test cases. Looking at lines 94-105, there's a test for custom getters that shows they should NOT be flagged:```kotlin
@Test
fun `Given an object val property name having a custom get function and not in screaming case notation then do not emit`() {
    val code =
        """
        class Foo {
            companion object {
                val foo
                    get() = foobar() // Lint can not check whether data is immutable
            }
        }
        """.trimIndent()
    propertyNamingRuleAssertThat(code).hasNoLintViolations()
}
```This test confirms that properties with custom getters should NOT be flagged. However, it doesn't have any test cases for annotated getters or getters with modifiers.Now I need to understand exactly why the `hasCustomGetter()` method is failing when there are annotations/modifiers. Let me create a test case first to reproduce the issue described in the bug report:

